Hi,

To do that, you should [focus the parent] container as many times as 
needed to reach the top-level container.
Then you can [split] as usual, and the window will be placed as expected.

There may be a shortcut to select the toplevel container (not sure), or 
you can use some large number of hard-coded "focus parent" commands.

[focus the parent]: https://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_focus_parent
[split]: https://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#OrientationSplit

-- Layus.

